HEADWORD: Abstersion
<hw>Ab*ster"sion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>abstersion</ets>. See <er>Absterge</er>.]</ety> <def>Act of wiping
clean; a cleansing; a purging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The task of ablution and <qex>abstersion</qex> being
performed.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abstersive</ent>⟦br⟧
